14 WHEREAS, the state has an interest in the safety of its citizens who are recovering from
15 addiction, and the Department of Community Health and the Department of Behavioral and
16 Developmental Disabilities need to understand how these facilities work and what best
17 practices are; and
18 WHEREAS, it would be beneficial for policymakers to study recovery residences,
19 understand the services they provide, and recommend possible solutions for improving the
20 safety at recovery residences and quality of the services they provide for citizens who are
21 recovering from addiction and their families and loved ones in this state.
22 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE:
23 (1) Creation of Senate study committee. There is created the Senate Study Committee
24 on Recovery Residences.
25 (2) Members and officers. The committee shall be composed of five members of the
26 Senate to be appointed by the President of the Senate and the commissioner of the
27 Department of Behavioral Health and Developmental Disabilities or his or her designee.
28 The President shall designate a legislative member of the committee as chairperson of the
29 committee.
30 (3) Powers and duties. The committee shall undertake a study of the conditions, needs,
31 issues, and problems mentioned above or related thereto and recommend any action or
32 legislation which the committee deems necessary or appropriate.
33 (4) Meetings. The chairperson shall call all meetings of the committee. The committee
34 may conduct such meetings at such places and at such times as it may deem necessary or
35 convenient to enable it to exercise fully and effectively its powers, perform its duties, and
36 accomplish the objectives and purposes of this resolution.
37 (5) Allowances, expenses, and funding.
